.TH "snd_card_new" 9 "snd_card_new" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_card_new \- create and initialize a soundcard structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_card_new
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ","
.BI "const char *xid "  ","
.BI "struct module *module "  ","
.BI "int extra_size "  ","
.BI "struct snd_card **card_ret "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
the parent device object
.IP "idx" 12
card index (address) [0 ... (SNDRV_CARDS-1)]
.IP "xid" 12
card identification (ASCII string)
.IP "module" 12
top level module for locking
.IP "extra_size" 12
allocate this extra size after the main soundcard structure
.IP "card_ret" 12
the pointer to store the created card instance

The function allocates snd_card instance via kzalloc with the given
space for the driver to use freely.  The allocated struct is stored
in the given card_ret pointer.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful or a negative error code.
